      <description>&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/espn-fantasy-football-api-2020/index_files/htmlwidgets/htmlwidgets.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;link href=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/espn-fantasy-football-api-2020/index_files/jsoneditor/jsoneditor.min.css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; /&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/espn-fantasy-football-api-2020/index_files/jsoneditor/jsoneditor.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;script src=&#34;https://www.dustysturner.com/post/espn-fantasy-football-api-2020/index_files/jsonedit-binding/jsonedit.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div id=&#34;its-that-time-of-year&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2&gt;Its that time of year!&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Its that time of year again. The time when we dust off the old ESPN fantasy football API R code and fix everything that broke in the last year.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here’s what I hope to show over the next few posts.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol style=&#34;list-style-type: decimal&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;How to access your ESPN public fantasy football league’s data.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;How to organize that data and create a few interesting displays.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;How to create a dashboard to supplement your league’s fun.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My ultimate goal is to build this into a package on Github. I’ve got that started, but its currently a work in progress.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
